         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/10/82 ¶  ¶ It may be just as well, dear Mr Ramsay, to mention, that Pterocladia lucida &amp; and Plocamium angustum are well known seaweeds, discovered long ago, and of wide range along the Australian c...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.10.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/10/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It may be just as well, dear Mr Ramsay, to mention, that <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name> &amp; and <name key="Plocamium%20angustum">Plocamium angustum</name> are well known seaweeds, discovered long ago, and of wide range along the Australian coasts, I collected specimens of both 30 years ago; so they are not new, though Dr J. Agardh stands sponsor to them It is as well, that I should mention this to you, because others might point out, that we had given old species as new ones.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Both these species were listed in Ramsay's note read to the Linnean Society of New South Wales on 27 September 1877, and published in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings of the Linnean Society of NSW</seg>, vol. 8 (1883), p. 402. He wrote </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.0071in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>the marine flora of Port Jackson and the <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>adjacent coast is worthy of special attention and research, several <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>new species and a new genus having been recently discovered on <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>our shores. The following species from Bondi have been determined by Professor Agardh, of Lund, the greatest authority on <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Algae: <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name>
                     </seg>, J. Agardh; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Splachnidium</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">rugosum</seg>, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Greville; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lederstedtia australis</seg>, J. Agardh. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">(nov. gen.et sp</seg>.); <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gelidium corneum</seg>, Greville; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Plocamium%20angustum">Plocamium angustum</name>
                     </seg>, J. Agardh<seg style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> You will find them noted in the XI. vol. of the fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>, vol. 11, Supplement 1 (by W. Sonder), pp. 18, 26.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Plocamium%20angustum">Plocamium angustum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pterocladia%20lucida">Pterocladia lucida</name>
            </p>
